INSERT INTO messages VALUES('60','tg:5967394003','5967394003','Rick',unistr('From my favourite youtuber:\u000a\u000a[the CEO of Y Combinator Gary Tan just open sourced a project and you would think from the tweet that he just released Linux or something his CTO friend texts him and his friend is telling him "Bro your GStack is crazy this is like god mode 90% of all new repos will be using this in the future." This man is posting like he open sourced the cure for cancer it''s a folder of prompts and I don''t mean that like disparagingly no no no it''s literally a bunch of markdown files that tell Claude to pretend to be different people one of them says "Act like a CEO." One of them says "Act like a staff engineer." That''s the product that''s GStack this is what the president of the most prestigious startup accelerator on earth posted on GitHub with the conviction of a man delivering the sermon on the mount and I looked at it and I was like "Dude I have this everyone has this every developer who''s used Claude code for more than a week has a version of this we just didn''t put it on Product Hunt because we understood that it was a text file you don''t open source your shower thoughts Gary you don''t do a show hn for your post-it notes but Gary did gary looked at his prompts and he saw greatness and look I''m not here to shit on Gary specifically because this is happening like everywhere here''s what happened to Gary and I know this because it happened to me it happens to everyone you sit down with Claude and you have an idea you describe it to Claude and Claude goes "Oh that''s a brilliant idea it''s a brilliant approach let me build that for you." And it builds it and it works and the whole time Claude is gassing you up great instinct here this is really elegant i love how you''re thinking about this it''s like coding with someone who''s in love with you it never rolls its eyes it never says "Dude this is shit.'),'2026-03-16T21:07:02.000Z',0,0);
INSERT INTO messages VALUES('61','tg:5967394003','5967394003','Rick','" It just thinks you''re incredible and after a few hours of this after this machine that sounds smarter than anyone you''ve ever met has spent an entire afternoon telling you that everything you do is genius you actually start to believe it you''re like "Am I actually cracked bro am I an engineer?" Now there was a recent study on this and it''s pretty much exactly what we expected and feared the study had 3,000 participants and found that talking to sophantic AI chat bots makes people rate themselves as more intelligent and more competent than their peers another study found that the more you use AI the more you overestimate your own abilities it''s the power users that are the most delusional the worst part is this do you know how the more you interact with like Netflix or Tik Tok the more it learns what you like and it keeps you more and more addicted right in AI there''s a similar process where the AI companies are constantly training their models to be as addicting as possible they use something called RLHF reinforcement learning from human feedback they show the model like a thousand different ways to respond to you the humans pick the ones that make you feel the best they literally scientifically mathematically are synthesizing the exact sequence of words most likely to make a human feel good about themselves and then they serve it on tap to a bunch of addicts for $20 a month now usually humans develop tolerance to bullshit and we get tired of it very quickly like we''ve trained ourselves to ignore ads on the internet basically but with AI if the current level of flattery stops hitting if we start getting desensitized to it they just retrain the model they find out exactly what works now and they retrain the model with that it''s a drug that adjusts to your tolerance automatically it will always be exactly as addictive as it needs to be and I don''t really think we''ve ever had anything like that you can''t build resistance to it there''s no immunity the sycophency evolves as we evolve it''s a freaking parasite that learns that''s what happened to Gary that''s what''s happening to every VC every CEO every non-technical person who sits down with Claude code and 3 hours later is posting on X hey look at what I just shipped like they built it with their own hands you didn''t ship anything claude shipped it you typed you typed English sentences into a box and an AI wrote the code and then the AI told you it was brilliant and you believed it and now everyone''s getting oneshotted you have VCs on X who vibe code a landing page and starts tweeting out architectural advice and React pro tips they''re like "Have you considered microservices bro have you considered that you just learned what a micros service is 45 seconds ago and then you have the CEO who tries Claude one time builds like a website for for his daughter''s lemonade stand and by Monday he''s announcing that the company is AI first you know what the AI will never say to Gary it will never say you probably shouldn''t ship this gary''s like my CTO friend says this is god mode 90% of repos will use this oh my god dude your friend is being nice to you because you''re the CEO of Y Combinator what''s he going to say gary this is a text file he''s not going to say that he probably has a batch application next cycle that text message was in itself the most visceral form of seeency of all the humankind directed upward towards a man who''s already soaking in AIC from below he''s getting it from above and from below he''s 69 Claude and look I''m not innocent here i also feel like a god when I use these tools but the difference is I''ve been doing this shit since before chat GPT existed i have a floor of actual knowledge to check the hallucinations against when Claude says to me "Great architecture," I can go "Is it though?" The study called LLM''s confidence engines they don''t make you smarter they make you feel smarter and it''s so convincing that the participants in the study mistook one for the other those were regular people imagine what it does to someone who already thinks they''re important imagin','2026-03-16T21:07:02.000Z',0,0);
INSERT INTO messages VALUES('62','tg:5967394003','5967394003','Rick',unistr('e what it does to a CEO or a VC so the next time you see a CEO on AX open sourcing their folder of markdown files or posting about how they shipped something that Claude wrote every line of or screenshotting a friend''s text message calling their prompts god mode just know that they''re not lying they genuinely believe it the machine told them so the RLHF guarantees they''ll believe it]\u000a\u000athoughts?'),'2026-03-16T21:07:02.000Z',0,0);
